name: Etsu-Botan
description: Peach Pink. Large to very large, loose peony form; stamens dispersed among petals. Vigorous, upright growth; leaves large, oblong. E-M. (Amplexicaulis × Japonica "Tama Americana'). (Japan 2005 - Shunsuke and Yukie Hisatomi, Fukuoka Prefecture).

name: Euganea
description: White. Large, peony form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. E. (Aus. 1958 - G. Waterhouse).

name: Eugene Bolen
description: ('Donckelarii Red'). Solid Red form of 'Donckelarii'. Large, semidouble. (U.S. 1945 - Bolen).

name: Eugene Lize
description: ('Lady Jane Grey'; 'Annie McDonald'). Light Rose Pink marbled and splashed White. Medium, semidouble to loose peony form. Slow, compact growth. M-L. (France 1908 - Guichard).

name: Eugene Stockman
description: Deep Red with deeper veining. Large to very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (Reticulata 'Cornelian' × Japonica 'Mrs. D. W. Davis'). (U.S. 1979 - Pursel).

name: Eugenia Howell
description: Deep Pink to Red splotched and flecked White. Very large, loose peony form. (Sport of Japonica 'Mathotiana Variegated'). (U.S. 1958 - V. T. Howell, Semmes, AL).

name: Eugenie De Massena
description: Light Pink veined deeper Pink edged White. (Sport of Japonica 'Don Pedro'). (England 1877 - W. Bull).

name: Eulalia Sally
description: See 'Lady de Saumarez'.

name: Eunice Buckley
description: Rose Pink. Medium to large, semidouble of flat form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1955 - Wheeler).

name: Eureka Variegated
description: ('Peppermint Stick'). White lined Rose. Medium, rose form double. Vigorous, bushy growth. M-L. (Japan to U.S. [Star] 1930).

name: Eva Dowling
description: Bright Pink. Large, peony form to anemone form. Average, open, upright growth. E-M. (U.S. 1960 - Beasley).

name: Eva Grace
description: Rose Red. Medium, rose form double. Vigorous, compact growth. M-L. (U.S. 1960 - Miss E. G. Sutton, Minden, LA).

name: Eva Ross
description: Ivory White streaked and splotched Cherry Red with Yellow anthers and Cream filaments. Medium, semidouble. Vigorous, spreading growth. M. Japonica 'Magnoliaeflora' × Japonica 'Ville de Nantes'). (U.S. 1999 - Frank Galloway, Bolivia, NC).

name: Evaland
description: Watermelon Red with veining. Large, semidouble. Average, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1960 - F. C. Landman, Gulfport, MS).

name: Evan Davis
description: Rose Red. Large, semidouble with fluffy petals to loose peony form. Average, bushy growth. M-L. (U.S. 1956 - Davis).

name: Evan Warriner
description: Medium Pink center with Darker Pink edged petals and White petaloids and Medium Pink rabbit ears with Yellow anthers and Yellow filaments. Large to very large, anemone form to semidouble. Vigorous, upright, spreading growth. M. (U.S. 2018 - Tom Warriner, Birmingham, AL).

name: Evangelia Kalafatas
description: Pink. Large, formal double. Average, upright growth. E-M. (Aus. 1989 - K. Abbott, Rossmoyne, W. Aus.).

name: Evangeline
description: Rose Pink shading to Pale Pink at center. Miniature, rose form double. Average, open growth. M-L. (U.S. 1957 - C. Rose, Temple City, CA).

name: Evelina
description: White. Large, loose peony form with large petals. Average, spreading, open growth. M-L. (U.S. 1959 - Wilson).

name: Evelyn C. Bellamy
description: Pink with Dark Pink stripes with Yellow anthers and Yellow filaments. Large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M-L. (Seedling of Reticulata hybrid 'Valley Knudsen'). (U.S. 2016 - Pat Johnson, Cairo, GA).

name: Evelyn Chace
description: Blush Pink. Medium to large, rose form double. Vigorous, open, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1969 - W. I. McGill, Adams Run, SC).

name: Evelyn Fulton
description: Soft Pink and White. Medium, loose peony form. Average, compact, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1959 - Fisher).

name: Evelyn Henderson
description: Blush Pink. Medium, semidouble with scalloped and fluted petals. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1961 - Mrs. J. Clairmont, Glendale, CA).

name: Evelyn Jernigan
description: White. Medium, loose peony form with upright petals. Average, compact growth. M. (U.S. 1953 - Mrs. E. Jernigan, Brewton, AL).

name: Evelyn Kilsby
description: Deep Red. Very large, semidouble with rabbit ears. Vigorous, upright, open growth. M-L. (Reticulata seedling). (U.S. 1993 - Pursel).

name: Evelyn Poe
description: White with a few Pink splashes. Medium to large, full peony form. Average, spreading, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1968 - Poe).

name: Evelyn Poe Blush
description: Blush, darker at center gradually shading to lighter color with two or three Pink markings. (Sport of Japonica 'Evelyn Poe'). (U.S. 1970 - Poe).

name: Evelyn Poe Pink
description: Pink. (Sport of Japonica 'Evelyn Poe'). (U.S. 1969 - Poe).

name: Evelyn Ramirez
description: Rose Red. Very large, semidouble to anemone form to loose peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1981 - Alfter).

name: Evening Glow Pearl
description: ('Ye Ming Zu' - Chinese Name). White washed with Light Pink with Golden stamens. Large to very large, loose peony form with a mixed center of petaloids and stamens. Vigorous, upright, well-branched growth. L. (Reticulata hybrid 'Suzanne Withers' × Japonica 'Kona'). (U.S. 2012 - John Wang, Orinda, CA).

name: Evensong
description: Medium Pink. Medium, formal double. Average, upright growth. E-M. (U.S. 2013 - Gordy).

name: Eventide
description: Soft to Rose Pink veined Deeper Pink. Large to very large, semidouble. Vigorous, upright growth. M-L. (U.S. 1987 - I. J. Mitchell, Melrose, FL).

name: Evetta Moyer
description: Light Pink. Large, loose peony form. Vigorous, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1961 - Mr. Moyer, Johnston, SC).

name: Exquisite
description: Pale Pink. Medium, single.

name: Extravaganza
description: White vividly and profusely marked and striped Light Red. Large to very large, anemone form. Average, compact, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1960 - Short).

name: Extravaganza Pink
description: Deep Pink. (Sport of Japonica 'Extravaganza').

name: Exuberance
description: Pink. Large, semidouble. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. (Saluenensis seedling). (Aus. 1971 - E. L. Ansell, Lilydale, Vic.).

name: Eye Bright
description: Deep Pink. Small, anemone form. Average, open, upright growth. M. (Japonica 'Tinsie' x Pitardii). (N.Z. 1998 - O. Blumhardt, Whangarei).

name: Eye Candy
description: Very Pale Strawberry in the center gradually nerging to Medium Strawberry on the outer edge with darker rays of Strawberry radiating throughout. Large, formal double form. Average, spreading, medium density growth. M. (U.S. 2023 - Grant Montana, Colonels Island, GA).

name: Eyes Of March
description: Deep Pink with Red veining. Small, single. Vigorous, dense, spreading growth. L. Cold hardy. (U.S. 1996 - Stephenson's Nsy., Willow Spring, NC).

name: Ezo
description: (Northern Folk). Pink. Large, single. See Higo.

name: Ezo-Nishiki
description: Variegated form of 'Ezo'. See Higo.
